---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — \brag pages"
  description="What is a brag page and why you should have one."
>
  <div class="max-w-6xl">
    <div>
      <h1 class="text-9xl tracking-tight font-semibold leading-tight mb-2 text-blue-500/15">
        About
      </h1>

      <div class="carousel-wrapper">
        <div class="carousel">
          <div class="carousel-track text-blue-600">
            <a href="#what-is-a-brag-page">What is a /brag page?</a>
            <a href="#who-came-up-with-the-idea">Who came up with the idea?</a>
            <a href="#how-to-submit">How can I submit my /brag page?</a>
            <a href="#how-to-remove">How can I remove my /brag page?</a>
            <a href="#how-does-this-work">How does this website work?</a>
            <a href="#suggestions">So... I have a suggestion!</a>
            <!-- duplicated for seamless loop -->
            <a href="#what-is-a-brag-page" aria-hidden="true">What is a /brag page?</a>
            <a href="#who-came-up-with-the-idea" aria-hidden="true">Who came up with the idea?</a>
            <a href="#how-to-submit" aria-hidden="true">How can I submit my /brag page?</a>
            <a href="#how-to-remove" aria-hidden="true">How can I remove my /brag page?</a>
            <a href="#how-does-this-work" aria-hidden="true">How does this website work?</a>
            <a href="#suggestions" aria-hidden="true">So... I have a suggestion!</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="leading-loose mt-10 grid grid-cols-2 gap-12 divide-amber-100 divide-dashed">
      <article id="what-is-a-brag-page" class="space-y-4">
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-500">What is a /brag page?</h2>
          <p class="w-4/5">
            A <span class="bg-zinc-100 px-2 rounded-sm">/brag</span> page is a personal page where you
            tell people about your professional wins<sup>(*):</sup> what have you shipped, what are you
            definetely the best at, what excites the most about your work? <span
              class="font-semibold">It is an evolving and opiniated record of your career.</span
            >
          </p>
          <p class="w-4/5">This is a collection of all /brag pages submitted by users.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-2">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-zinc-400">Isn't that what that blue app does?</h3>
          <p class="w-4/5">
            Not even close. That app is a platform that owns your data, curates your presentation
            and buries your wins in an algorithm. <span class="font-semibold"
              >A /brag page is yours - your domain, your format, your voice</span
            >. Do it as you please. Share it with us, please.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article id="who-came-up-with-the-idea" class="space-y-4">
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-500">Who came up with \brag pages?</h2>
          <p class="w-4/5">
            <a href="https://x.com/aarondfrancis" target="_blank" class="text-blue-500"
              >Aaron Francis</a
            >, the 2x dad of twins and father of <a
              href="https://soloterm.com/"
              target="_blank"
              class="text-blue-500">Solo</a
            > (not a Solo dad though, kudos to Jenifer) and <a
              href="https://x.com/IanLandsman"
              target="_blank"
              class="text-blue-500">Ian Landsman</a
            >, The Business Dad, initiated the talks about brag pages on episode 132 of The Mostly
            Technical Podcast.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
            <a href="/submit" class="text-blue-500 border-text-blue-500 border-b w-fit"
              >Listen to Mostly Technical Podcast</a
            >
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-2">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-zinc-400">Who built this website?</h3>
          <p class="w-4/5">
            This website was built by <a
              href="https://x.com/amarelodandara"
              target="_blank"
              class="text-blue-500"
            >
              Dandara</a
            >, a <span class="italic">mostly technical</span> designer.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
          <a href="https://adandara.com" class="text-blue-500 border-text-blue-500 border-b w-fit"
            >Check out her portfolio</a
          >
          <a
            href="https://adandara.com/building-a-home-for-braggers"
            class="text-blue-500 border-text-blue-500 border-b w-fit"
            >Read more about this website development</a
          >
        </div>
      </article>

      <article id="how-to-submit" class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-500">How to submit a /brag page?</h2>
        <p class="w-4/5">
          Open a pull request on the GitHub repo and add your entry to <code>brags.json</code>. The
          <a href="/submit">submit page</a> has all the details.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl text-zinc-400" id="how-to-remove">
          How to remove my page from the list?
        </h3>
        <p class="w-4/5">
          To remove your page from the list, simply <a
            class="text-blue-500 underline"
            href="https://github.com/nydndr/brag/issues/new">open an issue on GitHub</a
          > or better yet open a PR removing your entry from the data file.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article id="how-does-this-work" class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-500">How does this website work?</h2>
        <p class="w-4/5">
          I could tell you, but better yet, I could show you! It is open source, have a blast
          digging the <a class="text-blue-500 underline" href="https://github.com/nydndr/brag"
            >code on GitHub</a
          >.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article id="suggestions" class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-500">So... I have a suggestion!</h2>
        <p class="w-4/5">
          That's awesome! You can either open an issue - or better yet, a PR - on <a
            class="text-blue-500 underline"
            href="https://github.com/nydndr/brag">GitHub</a
          > or @ me on <a class="text-blue-500 underline" href="https://X.com/amarelodandara"
            >Twitter (@amarelodandara)</a
          >, the everything app.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .carousel-wrapper {
    position: relative;
  }

  .carousel-wrapper::before,
  .carousel-wrapper::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 3rem;
    z-index: 1;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .carousel-wrapper::before {
    left: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, var(--color-background), transparent);
  }

  .carousel-wrapper::after {
    right: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(to left, var(--color-background), transparent);
  }

  .carousel {
    overflow: hidden;
    padding: 0.25rem 0;
  }

  .carousel-track {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    width: max-content;
    animation: carousel-scroll 40s linear infinite;
  }

  .carousel:hover .carousel-track {
    animation-play-state: paused;
  }

  .carousel-track a {
    white-space: nowrap;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: none;
    border: 1px solid currentColor;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    opacity: 0.5;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }

  .carousel-track a:hover {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  @keyframes carousel-scroll {
    from {
      transform: translateX(0);
    }
    to {
      transform: translateX(-50%);
    }
  }
</style>
